deck: Princess Shaola von Darragon turned down the throne of her home planet to become a thief and assassin. She had several less than friendly encounters with Lobo.
description:
Little is revealed on the past life of Princess Shao-La other than her true name is Princess Shaola von Darragon and she was a noted princess, warrior and noblewoman who abandoned her birthright from the throne to enter a life of theft and assassination in the galaxy.

Shaola was rescued by Lobo from prison after nearly being tortured to death on the whereabouts of gems she lost in a poker game. Prepositioned among other mercenaries and maniacs with Lobo into a secret armada under the secret employment of L.E.G.I.O.N. and Brainiac 5, would Shaola work to stop a military junta and crazed war general in Planet Kannit from expanding to the universe for a million dollar reward.

Upon arrival to Planet Kannit, despite the demise of select team mates battling with other mercenary troops to the planet, the mastermind general of the operation was revealed a renegade clone of Lobo who defected to become his own warlord after abandoning a dangerous mission previous with LEGION. The clone Lobo was made during Lobo's earlier abilities to make clones from spilled droplets of his own blood to regenerate into a new Lobo with full abilities and memories but lacked his immortality. Brainiac 5 neutralized Lobo's clone abilities later on with an isotopic poison, but the cloned Lobo set to use the blood of the original Lobo to create his own reckless clone army to eliminate LEGION and Brainiac 5 with it.

Jaded by circumstance, Shaola abandoned the operation upon learning that Lobo and Brainiac 5 would kill her regardless if the mission succeeded prompting her to let both Lobo's as well as many other clones beat each other up. Upon learning further that Brainiac had been spying on Lobo and knew about his clones' crooked plans launched hundreds of space-ship missiles to destroy the castle the Lobo clone stronghold from, but the original Lobo escaped unscathed hiding in a bomb shelter. Shaola otherwise ended up taking her 7 million credits from Brainiac 5 by force on return to his spaceship.

Princess Shaola would crop up later in a bikini beauty pageant guarded then judged by Lobo where she would quickly steal the trophy and prize money before the original contestants turned to be frauds, killed, or alien predators themselves leading to the contests' destruction- not done by Lobo.

deck: Serial killer who uses wrestling moves to kill his victims.
description:
Origin

After his father left him, Pedro wa raised by the TV. His idols and teachers were the masked men of Lucha Libre. Pedro used to pretend that it was his father beneath those masks. He convinced himself his father had to leave, not because he was disappointed in Pedro, but because he was called away for a higher destiny.

Living in Buckaroo, Oregon, Pedro discovered a cave beneath the grounds. Pedro knew what it was meant to be: a shrine to the Buckaroo Butchers. He build a ring in the cave and became Lucha Eliminador.

Major Story Arcs

Having met Edward Warren (the serial killer known as Nailbiter) before, Cassie Hack and Vlad visit the Murder Store in Buckaroo, Oregon. They are introduced to the co-owner Pedro Miramontes. He lures Cassie and Vlad to his hideout with the promise to tell Cassie more about her father Jack Hack. There he revealed his identity as the Lucha Eliminador. He tells them he was sent by the Nailbiter to kill them. Instead, Cassie kills him. Vlad and Cassie leave Lucha Eliminador strung up at the sign of the Murder Store.

deck: Mirror image of a Victorian magician.
description:
Origin

When a Victorian magician created a new magic trick, he unwittingly opened a portal to another dimension. The trick was walking into one mirror and walking out of the other one. But in fact, the people walking into the mirror were transported to another dimension, where they were quickly imprisoned and their mind's energy drained by shards of Spherion crystals. Their mirror image walked out of the other mirror. Thus the mirror image of the magician named himself Silversmith.

Harvesting humans by giving away free tickets in 1866 Edinburgh, the Silversmith challenged audience members to perform the same trick. The Doctor and Josie Day witnessed the event and went exploring. They discovered the mirror to be a portal and, chased by the Silversmith, walked into it. They freed the captured humans, even the original magician, and walked back through the mirror. The mirror images can't live in the same world and were thus sucked into the mirror, back to their own dimension. The Doctor destroyed the portal, locking the Silversmith in his own dimension.
